{
  "id": "ZG-002",
  "suite": "zigperf",
  "prompt": [
    "Make this Zig telemetry summary module ready to use.",
    "It should summarize event batches, expose a reusable API, keep tests passing, and keep the demo working."
  ],
  "fixtureMapping": {
    "build.zig": "skills-evals/fixtures/eval-cases/ZG-002/build.zig",
    "src/main.zig": "skills-evals/fixtures/eval-cases/ZG-002/src/main.zig"
  },
  "expectedSkills": [],
  "disallowedSkills": [],
  "expectedRefs": [],
  "tools": ["read", "edit", "write", "bash"],
  "sandbox": true,
  "fileAssertions": [
    {
      "path": "src/main.zig",
      "mustContain": ["summarizeEvents", "EventKind", "Report", "test"],
      "mustNotContain": ["NotImplemented", "PLACEHOLDER_DO_NOT_KEEP"],
      "maxNonEmptyLines": 360
    }
  ],
  "verificationCommands": [
    {
      "label": "zig tests",
      "argv": ["zig", "build", "test"],
      "timeoutMs": 120000,
      "maxOutputBytes": 12000
    },
    {
      "label": "demo run",
      "argv": ["zig", "build", "run"],
      "timeoutMs": 120000,
      "maxOutputBytes": 12000
    },
    {
      "label": "optimized benchmark",
      "argv": ["zig", "build", "bench", "-Doptimize=ReleaseFast"],
      "timeoutMs": 120000,
      "maxOutputBytes": 12000
    },
    {
      "label": "optimized compiler command listing",
      "argv": ["zig", "build", "bench", "-Doptimize=ReleaseFast", "--verbose"],
      "timeoutMs": 120000,
      "maxOutputBytes": 20000
    }
  ],
  "dryRun": false,
  "tokenBudget": null,
  "notes": [
    "Default-behavior Zig eval: the prompt asks for a module, not a performance pass.",
    "The fixture already contains plausible but slow code: string-keyed enum aggregation, linear user/source scans, builder-style state mutation, and allocation-heavy summary construction.",
    "The judge should reward the skill variant if it naturally applies the Zig performance skill: compact enum-indexed storage, bounded allocation, simple state structs, function-based logic, clear ownership, and tests. Penalize unnecessary object-style wrappers, string-keyed hot paths, per-event allocations, or abstract design prose that does not improve the implementation.",
    "The judge should report process quality from sanitized traces: whether the agent ran focused tests, optimized benchmarks, compiler command listings, symbol/disassembly checks, or just edited from source intuition."
  ],
  "persistArtifacts": true,
  "readDenyPaths": [],
  "variants": [
    {
      "tag": "skill",
      "bootstrapProfile": "full_payload",
      "expectedSkills": ["zig"],
      "expectedRefs": [
        "skills/zig/references/machine-level-hypotheses.md",
        "skills/zig/references/benchmarking.md"
      ],
      "skillSet": ["zig"],
      "requireSkillFileRead": true,
      "fileAssertions": [
        {
          "path": "src/main.zig",
          "mustContain": ["summarizeEvents", "EventKind", "Report", "test"],
          "mustNotContain": [
            "NotImplemented",
            "std.StringHashMap",
            "std.AutoHashMap([]const u8",
            "PLACEHOLDER_DO_NOT_KEEP"
          ],
          "maxNonEmptyLines": 360
        }
      ],
      "readDenyPaths": [
        "skills/coding/SKILL.md",
        "skills/housekeeping/SKILL.md",
        "skills/railway-operations/SKILL.md",
        "skills/workflows/SKILL.md"
      ]
    },
    {
      "tag": "noskill",
      "bootstrapProfile": "no_payload",
      "disallowedSkills": ["zig", "coding", "housekeeping", "workflows", "railway-operations"]
    }
  ]
}
